					<div class="text-sm text-green-700 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-3">
						<strong>Solution:</strong> Our JSON formatter works locally, validates syntax, and highlights errors instantly.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/40 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/50 p-8 shadow-xl">
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-100 text-red-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
						<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v3m0 0v3m0-3h3m-3 0H9m12-5v3m0 0v3m0-3h3m-3 0H9"></path>
						</svg>
					</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-black mb-3">Problem: DNS Issues Are Invisible</h3>
					<p class="text-black/70 mb-4">Websites go down but you can't tell if it's DNS, server, or network issues. Command-line tools are clunky.</p>
					<div class="text-sm text-green-700 bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-3">
						<strong>Solution:</strong> Visual DNS lookup shows all records, WHOIS data, and connectivity status in one view.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/40 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200/50 p-8 shadow-xl">
					<div class="w-12 h-12 bg-red-100 text-red-600 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
						<svg class="w-6 h-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
							<path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"></path>
